OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1784638109
OL,3,CRare Titanic letter written days
OL,4,Cbefore sinking to go under the hammer
OL,6,FA letter written by a passenger days
OL,7,Fbefore he died in the Titanic disaster
OL,8,Fis expected to sell for up to #35,000
OL,9,Fat auction.
OL,11,FHenry Price Hodges wrote the letter to
OL,12,Fa friend, Hector Young, of the Newtown
OL,13,FConservative Association in
OL,14,FSouthampton.
OL,16,FMr Hodges boarded the Titanic at
OL,17,FSouthampton as a second-class
OL,18,Fpassenger and held ticket number
OL,19,F250643, which had cost #13.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
